<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Twilio Two-Way Call</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Twilio Two-Way Call</h1>
    <p>This is a simple Node.js application for handling two-way calls with Twilio.</p>
    <p>To make a call, you will need to configure your Twilio phone number to point to the `/voice` endpoint of this application.</p>
    <p>You can use a service like ngrok to expose your local server to the internet if you're running this locally.</p>

    <h2>Make an Outbound Call</h2>
    <form action="/make-call" method="POST">
        <label for="to">Call to:</label>
        <input type="text" id="to" name="to" placeholder="e.g., +15551234567" required>
        <br><br>
        <label for="connectTo">Connect to:</label>
        <input type="text" id="connectTo" name="connectTo" placeholder="e.g., +15559876543" required>
        <br><br>
        <button type="submit">Call</button>
    </form>

    <p>Your Twilio phone number is: <%= phoneNumber %></p>
</body>
</html>
